<item>
            <title>[LU-13709] &apos;lfs mkdir -i -1&apos; may not initialize target MDTs correctly </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13709</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When &apos;lfs mkdir -i -1&apos; is used to create directory with balanced MDT usage, it may not initialize target MDTs correctly, which will cause verify_dir_param() report &quot;stripe offset x is not in target list&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From 2.13 MDT object QoS allocation is supported, and these codes are removed, so this needs to be fixed in 2.12 only. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
